{"key":"post-13782481","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13782481</id>\n<content>Yes a timer.&amp;nbsp; In addition, don't let the cool mist blow directly against the shelf above.&amp;nbsp; If it does, the water will condense and drip back down, making a mess.&amp;nbsp; Put the humidifier to the side of your shelves so it can shoot straight up to the top of the GH.&amp;nbsp; By the time the mist reaches the top, it will have had time to evaporate into the air.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There should never be mist settling on your substrates.&amp;nbsp; If there is, reduce the run time with your timer, and/or cut more holes in the plastic for fresh air exchange and evaporation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>13781548</prev>\n<first>11023800</first>\n<last>13782481</last>\n<when>1294971643</when>\n<utime>01/14/11 04:20 AM</utime>\n</post>"}